RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 7150. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSTANGMAGNA rushed from outset to establish the inside position, was on even terms with a trio of rivals at the midway point, saved ground arond the turn, and shook clear of all rivals in the homestretch. CAROLS KITTEN contested the early pace from a three wide stance, maintained that three wide pose through the turn, and responded wel to urging to get up for place in final stride. FLASHY GAIL broke alertly, rated close up along the backstretch, took a two path journey around the bend, was the lone rival in second flight at the head of the stretch, then was nipped in final stride for the place honors. GODDESS OF WONDER lacked a needed rally after pressing the early pace and trekking four wide around the turn. EUROBOUTTOGETIT rated close up along the backstretch but lost ground to rivals by travelling widest of all.

ENTRY.NAME: Goddess of Wonder
ENTRY.OWNER: Parsley, Jean Ann and James Oakley

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 17600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OKLAHOMA STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INCA EMPIRE showed reserve in early going, swung to three wide long the backstretch and nearing the quarter pole, gained command in the closing bend, and drew clear in final sixteenth for a clear score. NEEDABETTERJOCK hustled from the break and established an inside pose, set the pace in tandem as the inside rival, was headed inside the half pole, and couldnt fend off the late charge of eventual winner in the closing strides. LIARS CLUB broke alertly and pressed the pace two wide through the opening half, angled out to three wide at upper stretch, then came up empty in final sixteenth. JACKS SPRING BREAK settled in behind the pacesetting duo while saving ground, was roused inside the half pole, but lacked a needed rally in crucial stages. DEL MOON was unhurried and failed to threaten while trekking the two path.

ENTRY.NAME: Inca Empire
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, three wide midway, drew clear

ENTRY.NAME: Liars Club
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace two wide, three wide upper, unable to sustain

BILLIE BABY forced the early pace from a three wide stance, gained a slight advantage and led the field near the midway point, was within striking distance at upper stretch, then was nailed in final stride for the place. RAINBOW SMILES broke in concert with rivals and set the early pace in tandem as the widest of four abreast, rated close up at the quarter pole and three wide at upper stretch before weakening in final sixteenth. ZATANNA Z trailed form outset and failed to threaten while doing so.

GOSPEL DANDY showed reserve early and trailed the field thorugh the opening half before improving placing with a three wide advancement at upper stretch. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CON SUERTE was unhurried in early stages, swung to three wide along the backstretch and through the closing bend, then wore down the leader in final sixteenth for the score. WICKED STREET rushed from outset and established a comfortable margin on the field, led all rivals into the homestretch, but was unable to sustain the lead in the final sixteenth. CALI settled in behind the speedy pacesetter, trekked the two path throughout, but was no match for top pair in final furlong. GOSPEL CARLOTTA showed reserve early by trailing the field throught he opening half before angling to three wide at upper stretch and passing a tiring rival. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEGA BOND pressed the early pace from between rivals, tucked to save ground nearing the quarter pole, gained command at head of stretch, and was inching away at the end. OUR CORNERSTONE settled into mid pack shortly after the start, saved ground around the first bend, advanced on the leaders inside the quarter pole, was in tight and bumped at upper stretch, and kept on to procure the place. OGA BEAR rushed from outset and led the field while saving ground, had a slight advantage and was bumped at upper stretch and kept on for the show. LASTCALLFORALCOHOL lacked a needed rally after showing reserve and rating back. HUNTER'S LEGACY lost ground to front runners with a wide trip. SHIPMAN'S SONG steadily faded after rating close up and three wide around the first turn.
